How the big companies are running out of breath:
Long before he led Apple's revival, Jobs had predicted with foresight that many of the industry's leaders would falter in their vision and lose their market share.
"Let's say you work for IBM or Xerox, so you make better copiers or printers, what's next?"
You have a monopoly on the market, so the company can no longer be a successful company.
