Among other things, its great availability.
Collserola is more complex", said the architect, for whom the name "Gates to Collserola" is a "lexicological trap": we must not think of them "as entrances to the park, but rather as a demarcation of zones where it is possible to act".
Modol, like Roldán and Bayona with experience in the world of urban planning, qualifies the proposal as an "intellectual challenge" with "some dangers".
The danger of "the uncertainty that the public space project represents today", after the experience of the 1980s in the Forum area, which had "its song swans".
The first concern is the very definition of where to build.
"To define something is to take the next step", that is, in principle, to go one step further.
