Bayona suggests that the question that gave the name to the game is complicated because the selection criteria lack Collserola's global vision: "There have been 16 selection procedures covering all the mountain-sea axis, but there is no longitudinal study that looks at the area and understands it as a whole".
That means that at least he signed up for all 16 auditions.
Otherwise, the design of one gate may conflict with the concept and definition of the architect of the next gate.
