This allows you to know if they allow you to follow posts, if they sign up for new accounts, if they have favorites, etc.
The new face of Twitter was tested "in August on a small percentage of users" before being rolled out to the entire network on Monday, Twitter spokeswoman Carolyn Penner told AFP.
Twitter, which was known for its little instinctive functioning, with terms somewhat incomprehensible (RT for the repeated dissemination of someone else's post, followfriday pour recommander de suivre un autre utilisateur) faisant le bonheur des initiés, s'ouvre ainsi a un public plus large avec un maniement plus comparable à celui des grands réseaux publics Facebook et Google+.
